Three armed men made off with an undisclosed sum of money after robbing Amalinda KFC on Tuesday evening. Police spokesperson Captain Mluleki Mbi said three men walked into the shop and demanded money from the cashiers and manager. “Three suspects approached the cashier and one took out a gun, one jumped over the counter and went to the back office where the manager was busy counting money. They took some money and fled in a gateway vehicle.” He said police were investigating a case of business robbery.